casebody.data:
THE CITY OF PASSAIC AND BERNARD GILLEN, COMPLAINANTS-PROSECUTORS, v. LOUIS GROSS, DEFENDANT-RESPONDENT. Decided June 4, 1923.

Before Justices Kalisch, Black and Katzenbach.

For the petition, Collins & Corbin (Edward A. Marldey and Charles W. Broadhurst, of counsel). Per Curiam.

The matter set forth in the petition for a rehearing having been duly consideerd, the application for a rehearing is denied.
